NAME
    gcloud beta container images scan - starts a vulnerability scan of a
        Container Registry image

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud beta container images scan RESOURCE_URL [--async]
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (BETA) Starts a vulnerability scan of a Container Registry image.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     RESOURCE_URL
        The fully-qualified URL of the Container Registry image to scan.

FLAGS
     --async
        Return immediately, without waiting for the operation in progress to
        complete.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

API REFERENCE
    This command uses the ondemandscanning/v1beta1 API. The full documentation
    for this API can be found at: https://www.google.com

EXAMPLES
    The following command starts a vulnerability scan of a Container Registry
    image.

        $ gcloud beta container images scan \
            https://us.gcr.io/my-project/\
        debian@sha256:6ea10209bda9af3c1260950b947715d6a3825d21d89e39889f4b9d\
        c5dc24a763

NOTES
    This command is an internal implementation detail and may change or
    disappear without notice. This command is currently in BETA and may change
    without notice.

